TAD, generating conformational ensembles with minimal overestimation of PRE eﬀects (Figure 3 and Table 1).
Ensemble-averaged distances between several pairs of
residues of p53-TAD have also been determined previously using smFRET and TR-FRET measurement71 (see Figure 4
and Figure S8). For the distances between residues 1 and 17 (Figure 4, top row), results from c22* and Amber ﬀ99SB-
ILDN simulations agreed well with experimental values, while ﬀ99SB-ILDN-TIP4P-D and a99SB-disp appeared to slightly
overestimate this distance. For another residue pair, 14 and 30 (Figure 4, middle row), all four force ﬁelds showed reasonable
agreement with the experimental data. However, caution needs
to be taken to interpret the absolute distance estimation from smFRET and TR-FRET experiments, since ﬂuorescence
properties and energy transfer also depend on environment and orientation of the dye,98 and the average distance inferred
from FRET can vary according to the model chosen to describe the distance distribution.99−101 Therefore, the
distances between these two residue pairs calculated from all simulations did not seem too qualitatively diﬀerent from

experimental measurement. On the other hand, the distance

between residues 10 and 56 was signiﬁcantly underestimated in

c22* and ﬀ99SB-ILDN simulations, while better agreement

was observed for ﬀ99SB-ILDN-TIP4P-D and a99SB-disp force

ﬁelds (Figure 4, bottom row). We also directly computed the

mean FRET eﬃciency from the simulated distance distribution

